    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-15T14:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-15T14:45:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/131: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-15T14:00:00-05:45"
                            >March 15, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s 25, March 11, 6 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d650fn18">Not
                        printed.</note> Salvadorean delegates returned to San Salvador March 15. It
                    is my understanding that the President did not receive them and that they
                    received no encouragement in their mission. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                    assured me that Nicaragua’s policy with respect to <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Martínez</persName> has not changed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
